"Capt. Henry Brace of West Hartford CT (per Findagrave). EH 396 calls him simply 'Henry Brace'; the 'Captain' title comes from Findagrave/Old Center Cemetery records.","mother_research_notes":"Elizabeth Cadwell Brace of West Hartford CT — Cadwell is the same West Hartford family Aaron Cadwell (X00910, husband of Mary Hooker H00986) descends from. The Brace and Cadwell families intermarried with the Hookers across multiple generations."},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H00396","children_ids":["H01022","H01023","H01024","H01025","H01026","H01027","H01028","H01029","H01030","H01031","H01032","H01033","H01034","H01035","H01036","H01037"],"date_year":1763,"date_month":8,"date_day":18,"location_city":"West Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","marriage_number":1}],"tags":["revolutionary_war"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909, entry 396"},{"short":"WikiTree — Henry Brace III + Abigail (Hooker) Brace profiles"},{"short":"Findagrave — Pvt Henry Brace III VETERAN (Old Center Cemetery, West Hartford CT)"},{"short":"Connecticut Rolls and Lists Vol XIII p.234"},{"short":"West Hartford Church Records"},{"short":"West Hartford Cemetery Records p.41"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Seventeen children with Abigail Hooker, 1763-1788","body":"He married Abigail Hooker at Hartford in 1763 and they had seventeen documented children between then and approximately 1788. Edward Hooker's 1909 genealogy entries 1022-1037 list the children — though crowdsourced records add and subtract from this number in places."},{"number":2,"category":"military","header":"Revolutionary War private from West Hartford","body":"He mustered as a private in the Revolutionary War from West Hartford — alongside thousands of other Connecticut farmers and tradesmen who left family homesteads for the Continental ranks. He survived the war and returned to West Hartford where he lived another three decades."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"